title: Irish rap group Kneecap's Liam Og faces terror charges for displaying Hezbollah flag
description: Liam O'Hanna, a member of the Irish-language rap group Kneecap, has been charged with terrorism-related offenses by the Metropolitan Police. The charges are connected to the alleged display of a flag supporting Hezbollah during a Kneecap performance at London's O2 Forum last November. O'Hanna, known as Mo Chara, is scheduled to appear in court later this month.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Canada in 'high level' talks to join US 'Golden Dome' missile defense plan: Mark Carney
description: Canada is in talks with the United States about joining the Golden Dome missile defense system. Prime Minister Mark Carney mentioned ongoing high-level discussions. He highlighted increasing missile threats, including those from space. Canada is also engaging with European allies on the ReArm Europe initiative. Ottawa aims to diversify its security partnerships.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Trump’s ‘white genocide’ claims ignore the reality of life and crime in South Africa
description: US president intoned ‘death, death, death’ as he waved articles purporting to show violence against white minority It was an ambush crafted straight from a reality-TV playbook. The Oval Office meeting with South Africa’s president, Cyril Ramaphosa, started with exchanges of pleasantries, before Donald Trump said “turn the lights down” and a video was played to support his false claims that white South African farmers are being murdered for their race.Ramaphosa came prepared with champion white South African golfers Ernie Els and Retief Goosen, whom the golf-mad Trump referred to as “friends”, as well as South Africa’s richest person, Johann Rupert. author: Rachel Savage in Komati, Mpumalanga, South Africa
